cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of a data center with heterogeneous servers. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper uses a Markov decision process to design an optimal policy for the data center. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper uses a policy-based Poisson equation to analyze the optimal policy. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper characterizes the long-run average profit of the data center under different service prices. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with optimizing the energy efficiency of a data center, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture.
